BSE, ATYPICAL CASE - ITALY: OIE
*******************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
Date: 20 Oct 2003
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Office International des Epizooties(OIE), Disease Information [edited]
<http://www.oie.int/eng/info/hebdo/AIS_75.HTM>

Bovine Spongiform Encephalopathy (atypical case) in Italy
Emergency report
Information received on 16 Oct 2003 from Dr Romano Marabelli,
Director General of Veterinary Services, Ministry of Public Health,
Rome:
Report date: 16 Oct 2003.
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory.
Date of initial detection of animal health incident: 27 Dec 2002.
Outbreaks:
Location: Rodengo Saiano, Brescia province, Lombardia region
No. of outbreaks susceptible* cases deaths destroyed slaughtered
1 / 9 / 1 / 0 / 8** / 0
Location: Buriasco, Torino province, Piemonte region
No. of outbreaks susceptible* cases deaths destroyed slaughtered
1 / 32 / 1 / 0 / 31 / 0
* animals 12-months old or more.
** 60 other ruminants present in the outbreak have been destroyed.
Description of affected population: one cow aged 11 years, Brown
Swiss breed, from a mixed production (milk and meat) holding and one
cow aged 15 years, Piemontese breed, from a beef cattle holding.
Diagnosis:
A. Laboratory where diagnosis was made: Animal Encephalopathies
Centre - Istituto Zooprofilattico Sperimentale, Turin.
B. Diagnostic tests used: immunohistochemistry (monoclonal antibody:
F99/97.6.7) and western blot (monoclonal antibody 6H4).
C. Causal agent: prion protein.
Epidemiology:
A. Source of agent / origin of infection: under investigation.
B. Mode of spread: under investigation.
C. Other epidemiological details:
- cases detected as part of the routine active surveillance programme;
- in the 2 cases, the immunohistochemical and immunobiochemical
patterns observed were different from those usually observed in
bovine spongiform encephalopathy cases. Noticeable differences in the
brain region distribution of PrPsc deposits were also observed.
Further details will be submitted at a later stage.
Control measures:
- animals from the affected holdings were placed under official
movement restrictions until confirmation was obtained;
- stamping out was applied including all progeny of each case.
Animals were culled and destroyed by incineration;
- screening;
In summary, all measures required by Regulation (CE) 99/2001 were applied.
--
